Defendant in custody.
The Court comments and sentences the defendant to the Wisconsin State Prison System for a total of six (6) years.  That is three (3) years initial confinement followed by three (3) years extended supervision, concurrent with any other sentences presently being served.
The defendant is found eligible for both the Challenge Incarceration Program and the Substance Abuse Program.
Conditions of extended supervision:
1) Pay court costs;
2) pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC;
3) pay the balance of $150.00 restitution to The Crossing, joint and several with Joshua Reed;
4) AODA assessment and follow through;
5) Assessment, treatment, counseling as deemed appropriate by the Departments assessment process;
6) Have no contact with Joshua Reed;
7) Before entering into any intimate relationship, the defendant must obtain approval from her agent;
8) Undergo mental health treatment as directed by the agent;
9) Maintain absolute sobriety;
10) Obtain her high school diploma or its equivalent.
The parties stipulate to credit of 312 days.
Minutes.

Defendant in custody.
